 :tx/rationale "ASSESSMENT FINDING: Incompleteness Component Baseline Masking — bilateral.rs lines 1266-1271. The I component uses 4-tier partial credit: falsification+coverage=1.0, falsification-only=0.7, coverage-only=0.4, neither=0.15 (baseline for formalized specs). The 0.15 baseline means even unfalsifiable, unimplemented specs contribute positively to F(S). If 50% of specs have neither falsification nor coverage, I = 0.5×1.0 + 0.5×0.15 = 0.575, pulling F(S) down by approximately 3.4% (0.08 weight × delta). The baseline was presumably intended to reward the act of formalizing a spec (writing an INV-* ID). But it masks the distinction between 'spec exists but is unverified' and 'spec exists and is partially verified.' FIX: Consider higher baseline (0.25) for specs with well-formed falsification conditions but no test — this rewards good spec writing without conflating it with verification. Or separate I into I_formalized (reward for spec existence) and I_verified (reward for test coverage) with independent weights. VERIFICATION: Compare I component with current vs revised baselines. Check whether the 265 untested INVs are inflating I through the 0.15 floor. INTERACTS WITH: F(S) stagnation (I is 0.08 weight — small but contributes to stagnation), verification sprint (reducing untested INVs should lift I from 0.15 → 0.7+ per verified INV), structural ceiling risk (baseline floor prevents I from reaching 0). TRACES TO: INV-BILATERAL-003, ADR-FOUNDATION-020 (falsification-first)."
